---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'Claude Memory Alternative — Portable, Project-Scoped, MCP-Native',
  description: 'Looking for a Claude memory alternative? Telepathine.ai gives you persistent, project-scoped memory that works with Claude, Cursor, Gemini, and every other agent — not just one.',
  url: 'https://telepathine.ai/claude-memory-alternative',
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'ArtemisAI',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Claude Memory Alternative"
  description="Looking for a Claude memory alternative? Telepathine.ai gives you persistent, project-scoped memory that works with Claude and every other agent — not just one."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  canonicalUrl="https://telepathine.ai/claude-memory-alternative"
>
  <section class="content-layer px-4 pb-8 pt-24 sm:px-6 sm:pt-32 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Guide</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2">Claude Memory Alternative</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude's built-in memory is a great start — but it only works with Claude. If you use multiple agents or need project-scoped context, you need a portable alternative.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-layer section-divider px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h2>What Claude memory does well</h2>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude's memory feature lets the assistant remember preferences and context across conversations. For single-user, single-agent workflows, it works well. The memory integrates cleanly into the Claude experience.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Where Claude memory falls short</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4">
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">Vendor lock-in</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude memory only works with Claude. Your accumulated context can't travel to Cursor, Gemini, Windsurf, or any other agent. When you switch tools, your memory doesn't follow.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">User-scoped, not project-scoped</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude memory is tied to your user account, not your project. When multiple developers work on the same codebase, their memories don't merge into a shared project knowledge base.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">No structured intelligence</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude memory stores preferences and notes. It doesn't have a Morpheus pipeline — automatic normalization, deduplication, supersession of stale entries, and progressive context injection.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">No agent communication</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude memory is single-agent. There's no way for a Claude session to relay findings to a Cursor session in real time. No channel-based communication bus.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">No self-hosting</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude memory runs on Anthropic's infrastructure. You can't run it behind your firewall, on your own database, or under your compliance regime.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Comparison</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);">
                <th class="pb-3 pr-4 text-left text-xs" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Feature</th>
                <th class="pb-3 px-3 text-left text-xs" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude Memory</th>
                <th class="pb-3 pl-3 text-left text-xs" style="color: var(--accent);">Telepathine.ai</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Works with</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Claude only</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Every major agent</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Scope</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">User-level</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Project-scoped</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Protocol</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Proprietary</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">MCP-native (16 tools)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Search</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Basic recall</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Hybrid (FTS + vector)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Intelligence</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Raw storage</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Morpheus pipeline</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Agent comms</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">None</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Signal Bus</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Self-host</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">No</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Apache 2.0</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">BYOK</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">N/A</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Every tier</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="opacity: 0.8;">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Data export</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Limited</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Full API export</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Works with Claude — and everyone else</h2>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Telepathine.ai isn't anti-Claude. In fact, Claude Code is one of our best-supported connectors. The point is: your memory shouldn't end where Claude's ecosystem ends.</p>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">With Telepathine.ai, your Claude sessions write observations to project-scoped memory. Your Cursor sessions read from the same memory. Your Gemini research sessions add to it. Every agent contributes. Every agent benefits.</p>
        <pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg p-4 text-sm" style="background: var(--bg-code); border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--text-copy);"><code>{`# Works with Claude Code via MCP
# Add to .mcp.json:
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "telepathine": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@ai-memory/mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "TELEPATHINE_API_KEY": "your_api_key_here"
      }
    }
  }
}

# Also works with Cursor, Gemini, Windsurf...
# Same memory, same project, any agent.`}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="surface-panel p-6 text-center">
        <h3>Your memory. Your agents. Your choice.</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Start free. 10,000 observations per month. Works with Claude and every other agent.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/docs/quickstart" class="btn-accent">Get Started Free →</a>
          <a href="/features" class="btn-ghost">See All Features</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
